    "body": "I pulled the Snappy Compression branch, debugged and found out we're good.\r\n\r\nIf I send each request 1 by 1, I can clearly see that a new stream is created per request and old stream was closed:\r\n\r\n```\r\n@@@ unit test sending request 1\r\n### Server side libp2p handle - num stream: 3 - details - [ { id: 'i0', timeline: { open: 1583124905402, close: null } },\r\n  { id: 'r0', timeline: { open: 1583124905412, close: null } },\r\n  { id: 'r1', timeline: { open: 1583124905418, close: null } } ]\r\n@@@ unit test received response 1\r\n@@@ unit test sending request 2\r\n### Server side libp2p handle - num stream: 3 - details - [ { id: 'i0', timeline: { open: 1583124905402, close: null } },\r\n  { id: 'r0', timeline: { open: 1583124905412, close: null } },\r\n  { id: 'r2', timeline: { open: 1583124905434, close: null } } ]\r\n@@@ unit test received response 2\r\n@@@ unit test sending request 3\r\n### Server side libp2p handle - num stream: 3 - details - [ { id: 'i0', timeline: { open: 1583124905402, close: null } },\r\n  { id: 'r0', timeline: { open: 1583124905412, close: null } },\r\n  { id: 'r3', timeline: { open: 1583124905440, close: null } } ]\r\n@@@ unit test received response 3\r\n@@@ unit test sending request 4\r\n### Server side libp2p handle - num stream: 3 - details - [ { id: 'i0', timeline: { open: 1583124905402, close: null } },\r\n  { id: 'r0', timeline: { open: 1583124905412, close: null } },\r\n  { id: 'r4', timeline: { open: 1583124905447, close: null } } ]\r\n@@@ unit test received response 4\r\n@@@ unit test sending request 5\r\n### Server side libp2p handle - num stream: 3 - details - [ { id: 'i0', timeline: { open: 1583124905402, close: null } },\r\n  { id: 'r0', timeline: { open: 1583124905412, close: null } },\r\n  { id: 'r5', timeline: { open: 1583124905453, close: null } } ]\r\n@@@ unit test received response 5\r\n    ✓ can handle multiple block requests from connected peers at the same time (53ms)\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnalyse: request 1 sent => create stream r1 => request 2 sent => stream r1 was not there and stream r2 created => ...",
