    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I believe the spec comes from libp2p spec https://github.com/libp2p/specs/tree/master/mplex .\r\nAccording to the spec, in order to half close, one side should send `CloseReceiver (3) or CloseInitiator (4) flag` and that's exactly what I debugged inside libp2p-mplex:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/75861771-6d18bb80-5e30-11ea-8dcd-c1a1b24c2750.png)\r\n\r\nWhat it does is to send `CLOSE` flag to the other side after we finish sending our request.\r\nSo I think libp2p-mplex does the job for us. (because it has to follow its own spec anyway :))",
